{"title_page": "1949\u201350 DDR-Oberliga", "text_new": "{{Other|1949\u201350 Oberliga (disambiguation)}}\n{{infobox football league season\n| competition        = [[DDR-Oberliga]]\n| logo               = \n| image              = \n| season             = 1949\u201350\n| winners            = [[FSV Zwickau|ZSG Horch Zwickau]]\n| promoted           = \n| relegated          = {{ubl|[[ZSG Anker Wismar]]|[[BSG Vorw\u00e4rts Schwerin]]}}\n| continentalcup1    = \n| continentalcup1 qualifiers = \n| matches            = 182\n| total goals        = 668\n| league topscorer   = [[Heinz Satrapa]] (23)<ref>''fuwo'', page: 93</ref>\n| attendance         = 1,837,500<ref name=\"Fuwo\" >''fuwo'', page: 23</ref>\n| average attendance = 10,096<ref name=\"Fuwo\" />\n| prevseason = [[1949 Ostzonenmeisterschaft|1949]] {{small|(Ostzonenmeisterschaft)}}\n| nextseason = [[1950\u201351 DDR-Oberliga|1950\u201351]]\n}}\nThe '''1949\u201350 DDR-Oberliga''', playing as the '''DS-Liga''' in its first season as the ''DDR'', the German Democratic Republic was only formed after the start of the season, was the inaugural season of the [[DDR-Oberliga]], the first tier of [[East German football league system|league football]] in [[East Germany]]. \n\nThe league was contested by 14 teams and [[FSV Zwickau|ZSG Horch Zwickau]] won the championship. It was the second and last East German championship for Zwickau, having previously won the 1948 edition under the name of SG Planitz.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.rsssf.com/tablesd/ddrchamp.html |title= East Germany - List of Champions |date= |website= rsssf.com |publisher= |access-date= 19 January 2016|language=|trans-title=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.dfb.de/historie/ddr-fussball/meister/ |title= DDR-Meister |date= |website=dfb.de |publisher=[[German Football Association]] |access-date= 19 January 2016|language=German|trans-title= East German champions}}</ref>\n\n[[Heinz Satrapa]] of [[FSV Zwickau|ZSG Horch Zwickau]] was the league's top scorer with 23 goals.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.weltfussball.de/torschuetzenkoenige/gdr-oberliga/ |title= DDDR \u00bb Oberliga \u00bb Torsch\u00fctzenk\u00f6nige  |date= |website= Weltfussball.de |publisher= |access-date= 19 January 2016|language=German|trans-title=DDR-Oberliga top scorers }}</ref>\n\n==Table==\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\nThe 1949\u201350 season was the inaugural season of the league.<ref name=\"Ddr\" >{{cite web |url=http://www.rsssf.com/tablesd/ddrhist.html |title= East Germany 1946-1990 |date= |website= rsssf.com |publisher= |access-date= 19 January 2016|language=|trans-title=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.weltfussball.de/spielplan/gdr-oberliga-1949-1950-spieltag/26/ |title= DDR \u00bb Oberliga 1949/1950  |date= |website= Weltfussball.de |publisher= |access-date= 19 January 2016|language=German|trans-title=DDR-Oberliga 1949\u201350 }}</ref>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n{{#invoke:Sports table|main|style = WDL\n|update     = complete\n|source     = [http://www.rsssf.com/tablesd/ddrhist.html RSSSF.com]\n|show_limit = 5\n\n|team1 =ZWI|team2 =FRI|team3 =DES|team4 =ERF|team5 =HAL|team6 =FMM|team7 =BAB|team8 =IND|team9 =MEE|team10 =STN|team11 =GER|team12 =ALT|team13 =ANK|team14 =VWS\n\n|win_ZWI = 20\t|draw_ZWI = 1\t| loss_ZWI = 5\t|gf_ZWI = 69\t|ga_ZWI = 27\n|win_FRI = 18\t|draw_FRI = 3\t| loss_FRI = 5\t|gf_FRI = 87\t|ga_FRI = 29\n|win_DES = 17\t|draw_DES = 3\t| loss_DES = 6\t|gf_DES = 67\t|ga_DES = 36\n|win_ERF = 15\t|draw_ERF = 5\t| loss_ERF = 6\t|gf_ERF = 58\t|ga_ERF = 30\n|win_HAL = 13\t|draw_HAL = 5\t| loss_HAL = 8\t|gf_HAL = 56\t|ga_HAL = 38\n|win_FMM = 13\t|draw_FMM = 5\t| loss_FMM = 8\t|gf_FMM = 49\t|ga_FMM = 48\n|win_BAB = 10\t|draw_BAB = 4\t| loss_BAB = 12\t|gf_BAB = 42\t|ga_BAB = 66\n|win_IND = 8\t|draw_IND = 6\t| loss_IND = 12\t|gf_IND = 38\t|ga_IND = 45\n|win_MEE = 9\t|draw_MEE = 3\t| loss_MEE = 14\t|gf_MEE = 38\t|ga_MEE = 56\n|win_STN = 7\t|draw_STN = 5\t| loss_STN = 14\t|gf_STN = 31\t|ga_STN = 45\n|win_GER = 6\t|draw_GER = 7\t| loss_GER = 13\t|gf_GER = 34\t|ga_GER = 54\n|win_ALT = 6\t|draw_ALT = 5\t| loss_ALT = 15\t|gf_ALT = 34\t|ga_ALT = 50\n|win_ANK = 6\t|draw_ANK = 5\t| loss_ANK = 15\t|gf_ANK = 35\t|ga_ANK = 60\n|win_VWS = 4\t|draw_VWS = 3\t| loss_VWS = 19\t|gf_VWS = 30\t|ga_VWS = 84\n|result1 = P |result2 = RO |result13 = R|result14 = R\n\n|name_ZWI = [[FSV Zwickau|ZSG Horch Zwickau]]\n|name_FRI = [[SG Friedrichstadt]]\n|name_DES = [[SV Dessau 05|BSG Waggonbau Dessau]]\n|name_ERF = [[FC Rot-Weiss Erfurt|BSG KWU Erfurt]]\n|name_HAL = [[Hallescher FC|ZSG Union Halle]]\n|name_FMM = [[BSG Franz Mehring Marga]]\n|name_BAB = [[Fortuna Babelsberg|BSG M\u00e4rkische Volksstimme Babelsberg]]\n|name_IND = [[FC Sachsen Leipzig|ZSG Industrie Leipzig]]\n|name_MEE = [[Einheit Meerane]]\n|name_STN = [[Lok Stendal|BSG Hans Wendler Stendal]]\n|name_GER = [[FV Gera S\u00fcd|SG Gera S\u00fcd]]\n|name_ALT = [[ZSG Altenburg]]\n|name_ANK = [[ZSG Anker Wismar]]\n|name_VWS = [[BSG Vorw\u00e4rts Schwerin]]\n\n|status_ZWI = C\n|status_ANK = R\n|status_VWS = R\n|class_rules = 1) Points;\n|res_col_header = PQR\n|col_P  = green1 |text_P = Champions\n|col_RO = red2   |text_RO = Club dissolved\n|col_R  = red1   |text_R = Relegation to the [[DDR-Liga]]\n\n|winpoints  = 2\n\n|note_FRI = [[SG Friedrichstadt]] was disbanded at the end of season and scheduled to be replaced by [[BSG VVB Tabak Dresden]] but the latter was unable to compete in the league in 1950\u201351 because it lost a large number of players to clubs from [[West Germany]]. The team was than replaced by [[SG Volkspolizei Dresden]]\n|note_ALT = [[ZSG Altenburg]] defeated [[ZSG Anker Wismar]] 3\u20132 in the relegation play-off\n\n}}\n\n==Name changes==\nEast German clubs were subject to frequent name changes in this era. The following 1949\u201350 DDR-Oberliga clubs changed their name during the off-season and in the season.<ref name=\"Ddr\" />\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!width=\"250\"|1948\u201349 name\n!width=\"250\"|1949\u201350 name\n!width=\"250\"|1950\u201351 name\n|-\n|SG 